-- Iraq Offers to Host Round of Iran Nuclear Negotiations
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i   a n d   K h a l i d   A l   A n s a r y
-- 2012-04-04T14:02:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/iraq-offers-to-host-nuclear-negotiations-iranian-tv-says.html
Iraq  offered to host the next round
of talks on  Iran’s nuclear program , according to the Iraqi 
Foreign Ministry ’s website.  Foreign Minister Hoshyar Zebari made the invitation during
a meeting with a delegation from the Iranian national security
council today, the website reported.  Iranian  state television  confirmed the offer to host the
talks planned for this month, citing an unidentified Iraqi
official. Ambassadors of the U.S., Britain, France and Germany,
as well as European Union representatives in Iraq, have also
been informed, according to the report, which was published on
the television station’s website yesterday.  U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton said March 31 that
negotiations between Iran and the five permanent members of the
United Nations  Security Council , together with Germany, will be
held on April 13 and April 14 in Istanbul. Reports in recent
days have indicated that the venue has yet to be confirmed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
